Reasoning: The paper proposes a computational framework for discovering new connections between domains to promote creative discovery and inspiration in design. The use of topic models on unstructured text ideas from multiple domains suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The application of the framework to a dataset from an online collaborative community suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of a graph to capture conceptual similarity between ideas suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG).
